An ad hoc committee set up by the House of Representatives on the ongoing nationwide #EndSARS protests against the now-disbanded Special Anti-Robbery Squad of the Nigeria Police Force has summoned the Inspector-General of Police, Mohammed Adamu. The IGP is to appear before the special panel on October 22, 2020. READ ALSO:  Strike: FG, ASUU meet today — Ngige The panel will also conduct town hall meetings across the country to take hear from Nigerians on the matter, Daily Times gathered. Details later…